$BNT supply is variable. Tokens are minted & burnt constantly to maintain ratios in the platform. This is a necessity of the design that allows LPs to only deposit one token and ILP.  There was a big $153mn ICO in 2017, with only half the initial supply going to the public. https://t.co/F1KZx4VL26

Unlike in @Uniswap, where liquidity providers (LPs) need to supply both tokens in a trading pair, in Bancor, they only need to supply one of them.  Bancor has a system that protects LPs from losses when prices in a pair diverge (Impermanent Loss Protection, or ILP).
